  "description": "The Podcast ECoG dataset provides intracranial electrophysiological recordings from 9 participants with 1,330 electrodes during natural story listening. This dataset combines high-resolution human electrocorticography with a naturalistic narrative comprehension paradigm, including preprocessed high-gamma spectral data, auditory stimuli, word-level transcripts, and linguistic features from acoustic properties to large language model embeddings. The resource enables investigation of neural mechanisms underlying language comprehension during natural listening.",
